   "source": [
    "# Zolai dataset \u2014 gap analysis & audit (post-clean)\n",
    "\n",
    "**Renamed from:** `update dataset with gemini ai.ipynb` \u2014 Gemini *cleaning* now lives in **`zolai-cleaner-v2.ipynb`** (`RUN_GEMINI_REFINE`). This notebook is for **measurement and review** after standard clean / soft / noise / optional Gemini steps.\n",
    "\n",
    "## What \u201cclear gap\u201d means here\n",
    "\n",
    "A gap is when **production use** needs text of type **X**, but your corpus **rarely or never** contains clean examples of **X** (or they are drowned out by other styles). This notebook helps you **see** length, language mix, boilerplate, and samples \u2014 not to replace human judgment on domain goals.\n",
    "\n",
    "## When to run\n",
    "\n",
    "After **`zolai-cleaner-v2.ipynb`** (and optionally **`zolai-dataset-combiner.ipynb`**), on the JSONL you will train on (e.g. `zolai_train_ready_v2.jsonl`, `zolai_after_gemini_refine.jsonl`, or `train.jsonl`).\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Pipeline place\n",
    "\n",
    "| Stage | Notebook |\n",
    "|-------|----------|\n",
    "| Clean + optional Gemini | `zolai-cleaner-v2.ipynb` |\n",
    "| Merge sources | `zolai-dataset-combiner.ipynb` |\n",
    "| **This notebook** | Audit / gap review (no training) |\n",
    "| Train | `zolai-qwen-training-v2.ipynb` |\n"
   ]
  },
  {
