    "## Gap checklist (fill in \u2014 production vs data)\n",
    "\n",
    "Copy to your notes and mark **Strong / Weak / Missing**:\n",
    "\n",
    "| Production scenario (how users will use the model) | In this corpus? | Notes |\n",
    "|---------------------------------------------------|-----------------|-------|\n",
    "| Example: Formal prose / religious text | | |\n",
    "| Example: Casual chat / social style | | |\n",
    "| Example: Mixed Zolai + English UI | | |\n",
    "| Example: Numbers, dates, places | | |\n",
    "| Example: Domain: health / education / news | | |\n",
    "| \u2026 add yours \u2026 | | |\n",
    "\n",
    "**Interpretation:** If a row is **Missing** or only **Weak** in dirty form, that is a *clear gap candidate* \u2014 fix with targeted data or filtering, not necessarily \u201cmore random web crawl.\u201d\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Optional: Gemini qualitative pass (small sample, costs tokens)\n",
    "\n",
    "Uses **`GOOGLE_API_KEY`** or **`GEMINI_API_KEY`** (Kaggle Secrets). Set **`RUN_GEMINI_GAP_REVIEW = True`** only when you want a second opinion on *possible* gaps from ~20\u201340 short lines \u2014 **not** a substitute for your checklist.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# 6) Optional Gemini \u2014 outline possible gaps from a tiny sample\n",
    "RUN_GEMINI_GAP_REVIEW = False\n",
    "GEMINI_GAP_MODEL = os.environ.get(\"ZOLOAI_GEMINI_MODEL\", \"gemini-2.0-flash\")\n",
    "MAX_SNIPPETS = 60  # Increased for more context\n",
    "MAX_CHARS_PER_LINE = 300\n",
    "\n",
    "if not RUN_GEMINI_GAP_REVIEW:\n",
    "    print(\"Set RUN_GEMINI_GAP_REVIEW = True to call Gemini (costs tokens).\")\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    import subprocess\n",
    "    subprocess.check_call([\"pip\", \"install\", \"-q\", \"-U\", \"google-genai>=1.0.0\"])\n",
    "\n",
    "    snippets = []\n",
    "    with open(INPUT_JSONL, \"r\", encoding=\"utf-8\", errors=\"replace\") as f:\n",
    "        for line in f:\n",
    "            try:\n",
    "                t = (json.loads(line).get(\"text\") or \"\").strip()\n",
    "            except Exception:\n",
    "                continue\n",
    "            if t:\n",
    "                snippets.append(t[:MAX_CHARS_PER_LINE])\n",
    "            if len(snippets) >= MAX_SNIPPETS:\n",
    "                break\n",
    "\n",
    "    key = os.environ.get(\"GEMINI_API_KEY\") or os.environ.get(\"GOOGLE_API_KEY\")\n",
    "    if not key:\n",
    "        try:\n",
    "            from kaggle_secrets import UserSecretsClient\n",
    "            u = UserSecretsClient()\n",
    "            key = u.get_secret(\"GEMINI_API_KEY\") or u.get_secret(\"GOOGLE_API_KEY\")\n",
    "        except Exception:\n",
    "            key = None\n",
    "    if not key:\n",
    "        raise RuntimeError(\"Need GEMINI_API_KEY or GOOGLE_API_KEY\")\n",
    "\n",
    "    from google import genai\n",
    "    from google.genai import types\n",
    "\n",
    "    client = genai.Client(api_key=key)\n",
    "    joined = \"\\n\".join(f\"{i+1}. {s}\" for i, s in enumerate(snippets))\n",
    "    prompt = (\n",
    "        \"You are a Senior Data Scientist auditing a 2GB+ Zolai (Tedim) language modeling dataset. \"\n",
    "        \"Below are sample lines from the corpus AFTER cleaning. \"\n",
    "        \"Analyze them for:\\n\"\n",
    "        \"1. NOISE: Identify web-scraping artifacts (HTML, JS, Navigation text like 'Skip to content').\\n\"\n",
    "        \"2. DOMAIN BIAS: Calculate the approximate ratio of Religious vs. General vs. Technical vs. Creative content.\\n\"\n",
    "        \"3. QUALITY: Detect sentence fragments, poor segmentation, or excessive English noise.\\n\"\n",
    "        \"4. DIVERSITY GAPS: What is missing for a general-purpose AI assistant?\\n\"\n",
    "        \"5. NEXT STEPS: Provide 3-5 concrete engineering actions to improve the dataset.\\n\\n\"\n",
    "        f\"SAMPLES:\\n{joined}\"\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    resp = client.models.generate_content(\n",
    "        model=GEMINI_GAP_MODEL,\n",
    "        contents=[types.Content(role=\"user\", parts=[types.Part(text=prompt)])],\n",
    "        config=types.GenerateContentConfig(temperature=0.2),\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    resp = client.models.generate_content(\n",
    "        model=GEMINI_GAP_MODEL,\n",
    "        contents=[types.Content(role=\"user\", parts=[types.Part(text=prompt)])],\n",
    "        config=types.GenerateContentConfig(temperature=0.2),\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    print(resp.text)\n"
   ]
